<h2>4) Decision tree</h2>
<ul>
  <li>If each client has separate domains and compliance standards, prioritize workspace isolation and permission controls first.</li>
  <li>If account managers need instant booking handoff, prioritize scheduling/routing tooling before extra campaign add-ons.</li>
  <li>If you deliver executive reporting, choose tools with exportable dashboards and clear attribution fields.</li>
  <li>If your agency has high operator turnover, prioritize SOP-friendly UI and repeatable template systems.</li>
  <li>If you service enterprise clients, choose contract-grade governance even if setup time is longer.</li>
  <li>If your client mix is SMB-heavy and fast-moving, prefer stacks that reduce configuration debt.</li>
</ul>

<h2>5) Top picks breakdown</h2>
<h3>Pick A: Smartlead + Chili Piper + HubSpot (Best overall)</h3>
<p><strong>Best for:</strong> Agencies that need clean routing and reliable multi-client operations without enterprise-only complexity.</p>
<p><strong>Avoid if:</strong> Your contracts require deeply granular audit policy controls from day one.</p>
<p><strong>Pros:</strong></p>
<ul><li>Balances fast campaign execution with structured handoff logic.</li><li>Supports team-level process standardization.</li><li>Works for agencies with mixed inbound/outbound workflows.</li></ul>
<p><strong>Cons:</strong></p>
<ul><li>Needs disciplined CRM field governance.</li><li>Can become noisy if each client uses different naming schemes.</li><li>Training burden grows with routing complexity.</li></ul>
<p><strong>Setup notes:</strong></p>
<ul><li>Create client-level naming conventions before first launch.</li><li>Use one routing schema template per client tier.</li><li>Document exception rules for reassignment and rebooking.</li></ul>
<p><strong>Alternatives:</strong> Outreach + Chili Piper + Salesforce, Salesloft + HubSpot routing.</p>

<h3>Pick B: Instantly + Calendly + SOP layer (Best lean team)</h3>
<p><strong>Best for:</strong> Boutique agencies with low headcount and straightforward handoff paths.</p>
<p><strong>Avoid if:</strong> You handle many enterprise clients that require strict controls.</p>
<p><strong>Pros:</strong></p>
<ul><li>Very fast deployment for new client pilots.</li><li>Simple workflow for one owner per account model.</li><li>Lower operational complexity for quick turn campaigns.</li></ul>
<p><strong>Cons:</strong></p>
<ul><li>Less ideal for complex governance at larger scale.</li><li>Manual QA overhead can rise as account count grows.</li><li>Cross-client analytics may require custom reporting work.</li></ul>
<p><strong>Setup notes:</strong></p>
<ul><li>Create a reusable onboarding checklist for every new client.</li><li>Enforce a shared QA gate before campaigns go live.</li><li>Review response quality weekly by client vertical.</li></ul>
<p><strong>Alternatives:</strong> Smartlead + Calendly, Apollo + Calendly.</p>

<h3>Pick C: Outreach/Salesloft + Chili Piper + Salesforce (Best scaling)</h3>
<p><strong>Best for:</strong> Mid-size and large agencies with mature RevOps and strict client governance requirements.</p>
<p><strong>Avoid if:</strong> You are still validating base offer/ICP for most client accounts.</p>
<p><strong>Pros:</strong></p>
<ul><li>Strong governance and role management options.</li><li>Better fit for enterprise vendor evaluation expectations.</li><li>Supports advanced coaching and operational reporting.</li></ul>
<p><strong>Cons:</strong></p>
<ul><li>Longer implementation cycle.</li><li>Higher process complexity for operators.</li><li>Requires dedicated administration ownership.</li></ul>
<p><strong>Setup notes:</strong></p>
<ul><li>Map object model and assignment paths before migration.</li><li>Run a client cohort pilot before global rollout.</li><li>Build audit and rollback procedures in advance.</li></ul>
<p><strong>Alternatives:</strong> Smartlead growth stack, Apollo plus Salesforce routing.</p>

