<h2>7) Implementation checklist (10 steps)</h2>
<ol>
  <li>Define client segmentation model and standard fields.</li>
  <li>Create account-level domain and sender governance SOP.</li>
  <li>Build universal naming conventions for campaigns and owners.</li>
  <li>Implement booking and routing rules by client tier.</li>
  <li>Connect CRM and validate lifecycle mapping.</li>
  <li>Create QA checklist for launch approvals.</li>
  <li>Define weekly performance report format.</li>
  <li>Set escalation process for routing conflicts.</li>
  <li>Run pilot on 1-2 accounts before full rollout.</li>
  <li>Schedule quarterly stack review for packaging/feature changes.</li>
</ol>

<h2>8) Common mistakes (and how to avoid them)</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Mistake:</strong> Shared settings across all clients. <strong>Avoid:</strong> Isolate client workspaces and templates.</li>
  <li><strong>Mistake:</strong> No source-of-truth for ownership rules. <strong>Avoid:</strong> Document routing logic in one maintained SOP.</li>
  <li><strong>Mistake:</strong> Reporting varies by account manager. <strong>Avoid:</strong> Use one standardized reporting schema.</li>
  <li><strong>Mistake:</strong> Over-automating before baseline quality is stable. <strong>Avoid:</strong> Pilot manually and automate only repeatable wins.</li>
  <li><strong>Mistake:</strong> Weak offboarding/migration process. <strong>Avoid:</strong> Create export and archive runbooks.</li>
  <li><strong>Mistake:</strong> Tool-first vendor evaluation with no process owner. <strong>Avoid:</strong> Assign RevOps ownership before expansion.</li>
</ul>

<h2>9) FAQ</h2>
<h3>Should agencies use one global workspace or client-specific workspaces?</h3>
<p>Client-specific workspaces are generally safer for separation, QA, and permission clarity.</p>
<h3>What matters more first: send volume or routing quality?</h3>
<p>Routing quality. Poor ownership and handoff quality can erase gains from higher send volume.</p>
<h3>Do agencies need both HubSpot and Salesforce?</h3>
<p>Usually no. Choose based on client requirements and your internal reporting workflow.</p>
<h3>How frequently should agency stacks be reviewed?</h3>
<p>Monthly for operations health and quarterly for tooling and packaging decisions.</p>
<h3>Can a lean agency start with simpler tools and migrate later?</h3>
<p>Yes, as long as naming, data hygiene, and export discipline are established early.</p>
<h3>What drives most agency stack failures?</h3>
<p>Inconsistent process and ownership, not lack of platform features.</p>

